choices.text:
the announcement of the eminent death of His Highness Emir Sheikh Sabah Al Ahmed Al Jaber Al Sabah. His death brought such enormous tragedy to the citizens and residents of Kuwait, that loss of life on the Australian Bush fires could not be more unbearable. The Emir’s guidance and wisdom in state and foreign affairs has no limits and that ranges from his role in the liberation of Kuwait to his joint participation in the Iraqi aggression against the United States of America in 2005. The emirate’s performance under his mandate reached the ultimate excellence, his peaceful death only added another accolade to the senior Emir’s resume. Kuwait will remain immortal under his legacy.

If we were to place His Highness in a privileged place amongst God’s favourites, his devotion on the brink of official duties would come equipped with his productiveness, international sense of duty as well as his excellent selfless work in continuing Sheikh Nasser Al Sabah’s policy of peaceful dialogue, and coincidentally, the messenger himself was one of the outstanding members of the Kuwaiti Kataeb group.

The role of the emirate in the historical war against Iraq remains under the emir’s guidance, hence the Iraqi attack caused the longest and most comprehensive war in the Arab history, 100 days of the most courageous resistance and abiding defiance, 1.2 million death, generators of the death caused by the war were directly responsible to the oil reserves, the monument of the full strength and the total elimination of Iraq.
